97
00:06:46,477 --> 00:06:51,989
So, again, the Hohmann transfer 
is the most efficient transfer

98
00:06:51,989 --> 00:06:54,233
from one circular orbit to another one,

99
00:06:54,233 --> 00:06:58,495
whether it's to go 
from one low radius circular orbit

100
00:06:58,495 --> 00:07:00,845
to another one with a higher radius

101
00:07:00,845 --> 00:07:05,024
or in order to reduce 
the radius of a circular orbit.

102
00:07:05,024 --> 00:07:07,196
One or the other, it's a Hohmann transfer,

103
00:07:07,196 --> 00:07:09,064
and that's the most efficient way to go

104
00:07:09,064 --> 00:07:11,427
from one circular 
to another circular orbit.

105
